  "text": "Firefox Content Security Policy (CSP) Enforcement Audit\n\nThe CSP enforcement infrastructure in Firefox is organized as follows:\n\n1. CSP PARSER (nsCSPParser)\n   - Header: dom/security/nsCSPParser.h\n   - Implementation: dom/security/nsCSPParser.cpp\n   - Primary class: nsCSPParser\n   - Main function: nsCSPParser::parseContentSecurityPolicy()\n   - Responsibility: Parses raw CSP policy strings into structured nsCSPPolicy objects. The parser implements a finite state machine that tokenizes and validates CSP directives according to the W3C CSP specification. It separates input into tokens and processes directives with their source lists.\n\n2. CSP CONTEXT (nsCSPContext)\n   - Header: dom/security/nsCSPContext.h\n   - Implementation: dom/security/nsCSPContext.cpp\n   - Primary class: nsCSPContext\n   - Implements interface: nsIContentSecurityPolicy\n   - Responsibility: The main CSP enforcement context that holds parsed policies (mPolicies array). Manages policy enforcement, violation reporting, and provides the XPCOM interface for CSP checking. Contains methods for reporting violations (AsyncReportViolation, ReportInlineViolation) and checking permissions (permitsInternal).\n\n3. CSP UTILITIES AND DIRECTIVES (nsCSPUtils)\n   - Header: dom/security/nsCSPUtils.h\n   - Implementation: dom/security/nsCSPUtils.cpp\n   - Primary classes: nsCSPDirective, nsCSPBaseSrc (and derived classes: nsCSPSchemeSrc, nsCSPHostSrc, nsCSPNonceSrc, nsCSPHashSrc, etc.)\n   - Key functions: nsCSPDirective::allows(), nsCSPDirective::permits(), CSP_AppendCSPFromHeader()\n   - Responsibility: Implements the directive-level checking logic. Each nsCSPDirective represents a parsed CSP directive (e.g., script-src, style-src). The allows() method checks if keywords/hashes/nonces are allowed, while permits() checks if URIs match source expressions. Handles violation data structures and utility functions for CSP string conversion.\n\n4. CSP XPCOM INTERFACE\n   - Header: dom/interfaces/security/nsIContentSecurityPolicy.idl\n   - Interface: nsIContentSecurityPolicy\n   - Responsibility: Defines the XPCOM interface contract for CSP objects. Declares constants for CSP directives (as enums) and violation types. This is the public API through which other Firefox components interact with CSP enforcement.\n\n5. SCRIPT-SRC EVALUATION FOR INLINE SCRIPTS\n   - Eval checker header: dom/security/CSPEvalChecker.h\n   - Eval checker implementation: dom/security/CSPEvalChecker.cpp\n   - Primary class: CSPEvalChecker\n   - Key functions: CSPEvalChecker::CheckForWindow(), CSPEvalChecker::CheckForWorker(), CheckInternal()\n   - Responsibility: Evaluates whether script-src directive permits eval() and inline script execution. The CheckInternal() function in CSPEvalChecker.cpp checks if eval is allowed by calling aCSP->GetAllowsEval() and reports violations via aCSP->LogViolationDetails() with VIOLATION_TYPE_EVAL.\n   - Additional context: nsCSPContext::ReportInlineViolation() handles reporting of inline script/style violations for script-src-elem and script-src-attr directives (lines 195-204 in nsCSPContext.h). The method CSPDirective::allowsAllInlineBehavior() (in nsCSPUtils.cpp) determines if inline scripts are permitted by checking for 'unsafe-inline', nonces, hashes, and 'strict-dynamic'.\n\n6. SUPPORTING UTILITIES\n   - Header: dom/security/nsContentSecurityUtils.h\n   - Implementation: dom/security/nsContentSecurityUtils.cpp\n   - Primary class: nsContentSecurityUtils\n   - Key function: IsEvalAllowed() - validates eval usage for system principals\n   - Responsibility: Provides helper utilities for CSP checking including frame-ancestor validation, eval allowance checking, and CSP frame-ancestor/X-Frame-Options verification.\n\nENFORCEMENT FLOW:\n1. CSP header parsed by nsCSPParser::parseContentSecurityPolicy() creates nsCSPPolicy objects\n2. Policies stored in nsCSPContext::mPolicies array\n3. When code attempts inline script/eval:\n   - CSPEvalChecker::CheckInternal() queries nsCSPContext via nsIContentSecurityPolicy interface\n   - nsCSPContext::permitsInternal() checks policies against directive via nsCSPDirective::allows()\n   - If denied, AsyncReportViolation/ReportInlineViolation reports to observers and console\n4. Inline scripts checked via nsCSPDirective::allowsAllInlineBehavior() which evaluates 'unsafe-inline', nonces, hashes\n\nKey architectural insight: The separation between parsing (nsCSPParser), storage/enforcement (nsCSPContext), and checking logic (nsCSPDirective/nsCSPUtils) creates a clean pipeline from policy strings through structured checking to violation reporting."
}

